    </altformavail>
    <originalsloc id="aspace_hzc210077n535as55417152939680">
      <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
      <p>Originals returned to the lender, Mrs. Howard M. Turner, Jr. after microfilming.</p>
    </originalsloc>
    <bioghist id="aspace_hzc210077n545as86548551205123">
      <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
      <p>Ernest Longfellow was a noted landscape painter and son of Henry Wadsworth Longfellow. Harriet Longfellow, his wife, was a painter also. They resided in New York City and in Magnolia, Mass.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <acqinfo id="aspace_hzc210077n561as70423232913857">
      <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
      <p>Lent for microfilming 1977 by rs. Howard M. Turner, Jr., whose husband was Ernest Longfellow's grandson.</p>
    </acqinfo>
